INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (1,1,'Mr WordPress','','http://wordpress.org/','','2011-04-23 21:54:18','2011-04-23 21:54:18','Hi, this is a comment.<br />To delete a comment, just log in and view the post&#039;s comments. There you will have the option to edit or delete them.',0,'post-trashed','','',0,0),(2,10,'LC','','','','2009-09-21 07:34:49','2009-09-21 07:34:49','>QR Code AR Demo ( Augmented Reality )<br /><br />http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I6MiJKgtbug',0,'1','','',0,0),(3,41,'frogo','','','','2010-02-06 17:58:04','2010-02-06 17:58:04','>One word for you mate ... sweeeeeeeeeeeet!  If you want my code to integrate it with Google Earth then let me know and we can try it Monday morning!',0,'1','','',0,0),(4,44,'Allusion','','','','2010-03-13 18:43:16','2010-03-13 18:43:16','>pretty incredible project. excellent work.',0,'1','','',0,0),(5,44,'noblestreet','','','','2010-03-14 19:27:27','2010-03-14 19:27:27','>Nice work! Is the jailbroken Iphone a must to be able to communicate with external sources?<br /><br />Arn',0,'1','','',0,0),(6,44,'Moof','','','','2010-03-14 19:44:45','2010-03-14 19:44:45','>Very interested if you are going to consider a writer/cloner addition to this project.',0,'1','','',0,0),(7,44,'Daniel','','','','2010-03-14 23:01:44','2010-03-14 23:01:44','>I&#39;ve not had a chance to do any iPhone development.  Is jailbreaking necessary, or can you see this working with Apple&#39;s SDK?',0,'1','','',0,0),(8,44,'Lee McColl Sylvester','','','','2010-03-15 13:16:14','2010-03-15 13:16:14','>What chip are you using for your hi frequency implementation? I need to be able to read MiFare cards.<br /><br />Thanks, Lee  :-)',0,'1','','',0,0),(9,44,'Bluedove','','','','2010-03-15 13:42:28','2010-03-15 13:42:28','>Nice job, <br />what annoys me is that iPhone must be jailbroken in order to do this.<br />I remember Apple was bragging about iPhone 2 that they will allow hardware developers to be able to use API to communicate with the port, none of that was true. As a developer I&#39;m very disappoined with Apple and planning to switch over to Droid platform.',0,'1','','',0,0),(10,44,'Oni','','','','2010-03-17 11:38:09','2010-03-17 11:38:09','>Some interesting comments. I shall try to address them as best as I can.<br /><br />1) Jailbreaking is needed as we are talking simple 9600 8N1 No HFC to the ID-12 RFID IC. There is no real serial access to the port and even if there was, root access is required in order to get access to the port. By default this isnt the case with iPhone apps.<br /><br />It is indeed possible, using a LOT more electronics to gain access to serial devices using the microphone and essentially, a modem but its much harder and only works at about 1200Baud. <br /><br />It is possible to fake a connection to the iPhone by using a 500K resistor between pins 1 and 21. The RFID reader is then registered as some kind of actual device that the OS knows about but I didnt have time to test this. Again, Apple has safeguards here to make sure your device isn&#39;t allowed.<br /><br />Long and short of it... jailbreak (unless you are an uber hacker and go modem route or pay Apple lots of money!)<br /><br />2)MIFARE is indeed possible and was my first attempt. To do this, you need a different IC which is more complicated than the ID-12. RS Components stock such a chip with an aerial and all the bits you need. Search for MIFARE on their page. <br /><br />The problem is that such chips require serial to BE SENT FROM THE iPHONE. I had a lot of problems with this but I&#39;m told that the iPhone will do this. It is likely that this is to do with the resistor hack mentioned above and that one needs to make sure this works. Again, I havent had time or inclination to do this yet as I have another RFID project. If people want this, see the videos on my Vimeo page regarding the little black box. This does MIFARE over bluetooth.<br /><br />3)not sure about cloners really. RFIdiot has a lot of good stuff on this. As its already been done theres no point me doing it again although having a portable RFID reader is a great idea. Currently, I have a MIR:ROR sitting on my desk that I plan to take apart. Modding the USB output from that should be easy. These units do both low and high frequency so check on eBay for one.',0,'1','','',0,0),(11,44,'Fabien','','','','2010-03-17 20:44:25','2010-03-17 20:44:25','>Wow this is great! I actually had an ID20 lying there because I couldn&#39;t get my PIC to work with it, I so need to try this for my door lock :D<br /><br />(a bit of a shame to use an iPhone for that though)',0,'1','','',0,0),(12,44,'Jason Pryor','','','','2010-03-31 18:07:24','2010-03-31 18:07:24','>What&#39;s the range on your reader?  Is it possible to increase the range to say 200 feet?',0,'1','','',0,0),(13,44,'Alias','','','','2010-04-01 18:29:45','2010-04-01 18:29:45','>Have you thought of implementing that or pushing it to the Android platform?',0,'1','','',0,0),(14,44,'Chung Man','','','','2010-05-05 12:23:13','2010-05-05 12:23:13','>can i write a app for using this rfid?',0,'1','','',0,0),(15,80,'ciaran-mooney','','','','2010-08-09 15:29:24','2010-08-09 15:29:24','>Can you print his off the Vinyl cutter??',0,'1','','',0,0),(16,44,'HK','','','','2010-10-04 09:29:51','2010-10-04 09:29:51','>To get data on Tx line from iPhone working, use a pull-up for the Tx line.<br />Let me know if it works',0,'1','','',0,0),(17,44,'Jonathan','','','','2010-11-22 00:16:06','2010-11-22 00:16:06','>Trying to reproduce your build and a im not clear on the level converter. At the start of the howto you say to connect hte id12 to the RXI but later on after the ipod cable guide you say &quot;The iPhone should be receiving from the TX-O pin on the board whereas the ID-12 is sending to the TX-I on the board&quot; which is confusing because the tx0 is on the hv side of the board and the iphone is lv.<br /><br />thanks!',0,'1','','',0,0),(18,106,'ciaran-mooney','','','','2011-01-27 12:36:40','2011-01-27 12:36:40','>I may need to pick your brains about this. Going to build something similar to keep my home-brew warm and toasty.',0,'1','','',0,0),(19,44,'info','','','','2011-01-28 13:46:16','2011-01-28 13:46:16','>We are trying to find some help in NFC for iPhone.  We have an iCarte and the SDK.  can anyone get in touch and help us ? engineroomapps.com',0,'1','','',0,0),(20,113,'Meirion','','','','2011-03-16 11:11:32','2011-03-16 11:11:32','>Be sweet to hook this up to an eye tracker to control depth of field...<br />ala http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lVaPzUGHhxY',0,'1','','',0,0),(21,114,'handee','','','','2011-03-16 19:49:22','2011-03-16 19:49:22','>Ben, you&#39;re a star:) Now I want to play with it too!!!',0,'1','','',0,0),(22,71,'George Chriss','','','','2011-04-06 07:07:18','2011-04-06 07:07:18','>Happy to provide feedback, but the demo link is broken...<br /><br />[ http://identi.ca/openvideopro ]',0,'1','','',0,0),(23,66,'Yoeran','','','','2011-04-08 07:59:11','2011-04-08 07:59:11','>I saw this post is from a year ago, but hopefully you can enlighten me; You managed to record video with audio by using Arduino and GStreamer for Windows?<br /><br />What&#39;s the role for the Arduino in this one? Purely for interaction purposes?<br />Do you happen to have some example code to share? I&#39;m planning to build a kind of video booth where visitors can leave a short movie-message of about 60 seconds. I was looking into Cinder, openFrameworks and Flash and such, but can&#39;t manage to get it to work on either of them.<br /><br />Thanks in advance!',0,'1','','',0,0),(24,100,'Tameka Mckirgan','Laurente@fatmagulun-sucu-ne.com','http://www.fatmagulun-sucu-ne.com','202.43.178.41','2011-04-28 23:21:42','2011-04-28 23:21:42','I\'ve been browsing online more than 3 hours today, yet I never found any interesting article like yours. It is pretty worth enough for me. In my view, if all website owners and bloggers made good content as you did, the net will be a lot more useful than ever before.',0,'trash','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; de; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)','',0,0),(25,7,'Telstra mobile phone','Landolfi@hotmail.com.au','http://www.telefirm.com.au','79.129.222.225','2011-04-29 21:08:09','2011-04-29 21:08:09','Just wish to say your article is as surprising. The clarity in your post is just spectacular and i could assume you\'re an expert on this subject. Well with your permission allow me to grab your RSS feed to keep up to date with forthcoming post. Thanks a million and please carry on the rewarding work.',0,'trash','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; en) Opera 8.50','',0,0),(26,122,'kunde','kunde@mail.ru','http://www.ostensuedenwesten.de','199.15.234.211','2011-04-30 02:11:06','2011-04-30 02:11:06','Lots of excellent reading here, many thanks! I was browsing on yahoo when I identified your submit, I’m going to add your feed to Google Reader, I look forward to a lot more from you.',0,'trash','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; Deepnet Explorer 1.5.0; .NET CLR 1.0.3705)','',0,0),(27,116,'Bukkake Espanol','Pangilinan@ymail.com','http://bukkakeespanol.com/fayna-vergara-porn-star-2/','173.234.59.10','2011-05-01 22:00:43','2011-05-01 22:00:43','Excellent blog by the way . Very Nice Lay out and design . Very good execution on this on mate .',0,'trash','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; it-IT; rv:1.9.0.2) Gecko/2008092313 Ubuntu/9.25 (jaunty) Firefox/3.8','',0,0),(28,105,'fatmagulun sucu ne 24 bolum fragmani','Trosen@fatmagulun-sucu-ne.com','http://www.fatmagulun-sucu-ne.com','178.79.129.242','2011-05-02 00:48:32','2011-05-02 00:48:32','Hey there,  You\'ve done an incredible job. I’ll certainly digg it and personally recommend to my friends. I\'m sure they will be benefited from this website.',0,'trash','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; en) Opera 8.50','',0,0),(29,102,'husky dog training','meganx_152@yahoo.com','http://www.dogtrainingtown.com/husky-dog-training-tips.html','71.192.220.85','2011-05-02 15:36:53','2011-05-02 15:36:53','[...] &gt;First Kinect Playing | Section9 Lab [...]',0,'trash','Opera/7.51 (Windows NT 5.1; U) [en]','',0,0),(30,82,'best price for water front home','Domin7@gmail.com','http://www.welcomebeach.com/night-life-in-south-beach','184.82.186.128','2011-05-03 14:54:59','2011-05-03 14:54:59','Situated on the southern peninsula of Bahama Cay, this exclusive project fronts onto a pristine beach leading into crystal clear warm seas.',0,'trash','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; en) Opera 8.50','',0,0),(31,31,'Miami Night life','Dally@ymail.com','http://propertysouthbeach.ww.bs/1bed_condo_bahama.shtml','184.82.186.129','2011-05-03 14:54:59','2011-05-03 14:54:59','Situated on the southern peninsula of Bahama Cay, this exclusive project fronts onto a pristine beach leading into crystal clear warm seas.',0,'trash','Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; Media Center PC 6.0; InfoPath.2; MS-RTC LM 8)','',0,0);
